{
  "texts": [
    "This performance is closely contended by ChatGPT 4.0's 86.4%, showcasing its own breadth of knowledge [6].Further, Gemini's capability in complex reasoning is evidenced by an 83.6% score in the Big-Bench Hard benchmark, which poses challenging tasks requiring multi-step reasoning, a foundational skill for effective environmental management.",
    "It parallels ChatGPT 4.0's 83.1%, indicating both systems' aptitude for intricate problem-solving.",
    "In reading comprehension, as measured by the DROP benchmark, Gemini achieves an 82.4% F1 score, suggesting a nuanced understanding of text, a critical factor for interpreting scientific literature and reports [6].In mathematical reasoning, the Gemini model outperforms with a 94.4% score in the GSM8K benchmark, which includes basic arithmetic and grade school math problems, compared to ChatGPT 4.0's competent 92.0%.",
    "This indicates a significant advantage in tasks that require numerical analysis, an essential component in modeling and quantifying environmental data.",
    "Some findings state that ChatGPT 4.0 outperforms Gemini in terms of processing detailed text in images, demonstrating its potential for enhancing multimodal assessments in education [7], whereas some findings state that Gemini Pro outperforms GPT in terms of long and complex reasoning tasks and generating text in other languages [8].The development and application of Artificial Intelligence (AI) have rapidly advanced in recent decades, transforming from a theoretical concept to a pervasive force impacting various aspects of our lives, including education [1]."
  ]
}